
-- 8_50

  + A Virtual type do not get persisted over MongoDB
  + Case where this is useful
    - We have 2 field in our schema (Example posts & postCount)
      In this case, we need to update postCount everytime we add new posts which
      is not an elegant solution. In this case, postCount can be made a virtual type 8_50
      A virtual type is stored in the server where mongoose code is running